  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Kyrgyzstan: Enhancing Migrants&#x2019; Awareness on Air Pollution and Moving Towards a &#x201C;Healthy City Vision&#x201D; in Bishkek</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will contribute to the fight against air pollution and adoption of the &#x2018;Healthy City Vision&#x2019; through enhancing migrants&#x2019; and other stakeholders&#x2019; awareness of air pollution and its impacts on the communities of migrants living in Bishkek. This entails three steps. Firstly, migrants will be better equipped to take action in their communities to reduce air pollution owed to increased awareness. This will be achieved through an assessment of factors contributing to air pollution in the new settlements where migrants live, organizing training and community events for migrants and host communities, producing and disseminating culturally and gender-sensitive IEC materials via social media outlets and during the events, as well as supporting migrants&#x2019; community health and environmental projects. Secondly, relevant government officials and other stakeholders will recognize the role of migrants and commit to including migrants in the &#x201C;Healthy City Vision&#x201D; through training of government representatives on ways to reduce air pollution, as well as building a municipality-led Task Force that will comprise of government representatives, civil society, academia, and experts. Finally, trained migrant leaders and government representatives will engage in the existing dialogue platforms on air pollution and public health initiatives and present their community projects as effective models.</narrative>
  </description>
